  -Body '{"timeoutMs":5000}'

If it works, you should see devices respond.

Important Windows settings

Because BACnet/IP uses UDP 47808, check these:

Windows Firewall allows Node.js.
Your laptop/server is on the same subnet as the controller.
You are connected to the correct Ethernet adapter.
No VPN is stealing broadcast traffic.
Backend binds to the right NIC.

Set this in .env if needed:

BACNET_PORT=47808
BACNET_INTERFACE=192.168.1.100
BACNET_BROADCAST_ADDRESS=192.168.1.255
BACNET_APDU_TIMEOUT_MS=6000

Replace 192.168.1.100 with your computer’s Ethernet IP.

